Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

== Roasted Vegetables ==

Toss broccoli on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread broccoli out across entire sheet. Add carrots to a separate baking sheet; roast broccoli on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Beef ==

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining chili flakes, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings); simmer until bubbling and slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

== To Serve ==

Slice beef crosswise.

Add beef to pan with sauce and toss to coat.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain and toss with sauce as instructed.

Divide carrots, broccoli, and glazed beef between plates. Drizzle any remaining sauce from pan over beef. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.